<TITLE> Please also advise us: Sahara </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com)Home minister Sahara Khatun on Thursday invited suggestions from journalists alongside criticism. She called on the media owners to provide crime reporters with risk allowance. "We have always been emphasising the relationship between law enforcers and journalists. We will be able to create a digital Bangladesh with the help of journalists." She called on reporters to work with honesty and transparency, uphold the dignity of the profession at a programme of Crime Reporters Association of Bangladesh in Dhaka. State minister for home Tanjim Ahmed, inspector general of police Noor Mohammad, chairman of Standard Bank Kazi Akramuddin Ahmed, Dhaka Metropolitan Police commissioner AKM Shahidul Haque were among those who spoke. Tanjim said, "We ordered the relevant officials to see to it that journalists are not tortured." bdne
